&lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/philosophy/texts/state-time-and-event-survey/>
  rdf:type schema:Article ;
  schema:url &lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/philosophy/texts/state-time-and-event-survey/> ;
  schema:name "State, Time, and Event: A Survey of Substance and Process Accounts" ;
  schema:description "Survey of philosophical accounts of state, time, and event — examining substance and process traditions, from McTaggart's A-series and B-series to Whitehead's actual occasions, Buddhist momentariness, and process philosophy. Addresses the interrelation of permanence and change across Western analytic philosophy, continental philosophy, and non-Western traditions." ;
